  "title": "Accounts Executive (Full Sets) | Paya Lebar | Up to $3.3K + Bonus",
  "description": "<ul><li><p>Basic up to <strong>$3,300</strong> + Variable Bonus.</p></li><li><p>Receive a <strong>$100 reward</strong> for every 3 consecutive months with no MC applied.</p></li><li><p>Located at <strong>Paya Lebar</strong>, just a short walk from <strong>Paya Lebar MRT</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Monday to Friday, <strong>10:00 AM – 7:00 PM</strong> (Perfect for avoiding the early morning rush).</p></li><li><p>14 days of Annual Leave.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>We are seeking a meticulous Accounts Executive to manage our <strong>full sets of accounts</strong>. You will be responsible for the entire accounting cycle, from daily transaction processing to month-end closing and financial reporting.</p><h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Prepare journal entries and maintain the general ledger to ensure financial accuracy.</p></li><li><p>Assist with the month-end and year-end closing processes.</p></li><li><p>Perform bank reconciliations and reconcile key balance sheet accounts.</p></li><li><p>Efficiently process accounts payable (AP) and accounts receivable (AR) transactions.</p></li><li><p>Support audit requests, financial reporting, and ensure all documentation complies with accounting policies.</p></li><li><p>Support management with special projects and ad hoc reporting as required.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>At least <strong>1 year of experience in handling full sets of accounts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>Diploma or Degree</strong> in Accountancy or a related field.</p></li></ul>",
